rl=https://au.sports.yahoo.com/rugby/a/31649037/sonny-bill-williams-awarded-top-sporting-prize/|accessdate=20 May 2016|work=Yahoo New Zealand|date=19 May 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Team===\n* [[2004 NRL season|2004]]: [[National Rugby League|NRL]] Premiership with the [[Canterbury-Bankstown Bulldogs|Bulldogs]] \n* 2010: [[Ranfurly Shield]] winner with [[Canterbury Rugby Football Union|Canterbury]] \n* [[2010 ITM Cup|2010]]: [[ITM Cup]] winner with Canterbury\n* 2011: [[Bledisloe Cup]] winner with [[New Zealand national rugby union team|New Zealand]] \n* [[2011 Rugby World Cup|2011]]: [[Rugby World Cup]] winner with New Zealand\n* [[2012 Super Rugby season|2012]]: [[Super Rugby]] winner with the [[Chiefs (rugby union)|Chiefs]]\n* 2012: [[Bledisloe Cup]] winner with New Zealand\n* [[2013 NRL season|2013]]: [[Minor Premiership]] with the [[Sydney Roosters]]\n* 2013: [[National Rugby League|NRL Premiership]] with the [[Sydney Roosters]]\n* [[2014 World Club Challenge|2014]]: [[World Club Challenge]] winner with the [[Sydney Roosters]]\n* [[2014 NRL season|2014]]: [[Minor Premiership]] with the [[Sydney Roosters]]\n* 2015: [[Canterbury-Bankstown Bulldogs|Bulldogs]] Team of the Decade (2005\u20132014) \u2013 as a back-rower<ref>{{cite news|author1=Adrian Proszenko|title=Sonny Bill Williams named in Canterbury Bulldogs team of the decade|url=http://www.smh.com.au/rugby-league/league-news/sonny-bill-williams-named-in-canterbury-bulldogs-team-of-the-decade-20150801-gipebj.html|accessdate=2 August 2015|work=Sydney Morning Herald|date=1 August 2015}}</ref>\n*[[2015 Rugby World Cup|2015]]: [[Rugby World Cup]] winner with New Zealand\n*[[2015\u201316 World Rugby Sevens Series|2016]]: [[2016 Wellington Sevens|Wellington Sevens]] Champion with [[New Zealand national rugby sevens team|New Zealand]]\n*2016: [[2016 Sydney Sevens|Sydney Sevens]] Champion with New Zealand\n*2017: Won [[British & Irish Lions]] tour game with the Blues\n*2017: Drawn [[British & Irish Lions]] Test series with New Zealand\n*2017: Won [[Bledisloe Cup]] and [[the Rugby Championship]] with New Zealand\n*2017: Won [[Dave Gallaher Trophy]] with New Zealand\n*2019: Won [[Freedom Cup]] with New Zealand\n*2019: Won [[Bledisloe Cup]] with New Zealand\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|New Zealand|Sports|Martial arts}}\n* [[List of players who have converted from one football code to another]]\n* [[Sonny Wool]]\n{{clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*{{Cite book\n| last = Matheson\n| first = John\n| authorlink =\n| author2 =\n| title = Sonny Bill Williams: The Story of Rugby's New Superstar\n| publisher = [[HarperCollins]] Publishers New Zealand\n| year = 2011\n| location =\n| page = 144\n| url = http://naturebeebookclub.wordpress.com/2011/08/25/sonny-bill-williams-the-story-of-rugbys-new-superstar-matheson-john/\n| doi =\n| id =\n| isbn = 9781869508623}}\n*{{Cite book\n| last = Riley\n| first = David\n| authorlink =\n| author2 =\n| title = Off Loading with Sonny Bill Williams\n| publisher = [[Smashwords]]\n| year = 2013\n| location =\n| page = 70\n| url = http://www.smashwords.com/books/view/371003\n| doi =\n| id =\n| isbn = 9781311082213}}\n*{{Cite book\n |last        = Kent\n |first       = Paul\n |authorlink  = Paul Kent (journalist)\n |author2     = \n |title       = Sonny Ball \u2013 The Legend of Sonny Bill Williams\n |publisher   = [[Macmillan Publishers|Macmillan Australia]]\n |year        = 2015\n |location    = \n |page        = 368\n |url         = http://www.panmacmillan.com.au/display_title.asp?ISBN=9781743534212&Author=Kent,%20Paul\n |doi         = \n |id          = \n |isbn        = 9781743539200\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20150712121950/http://www.panmacmillan.com.au/display_title.asp?ISBN=9781743534212&Author=Kent,%20Paul\n |archivedate = 12 July 2015\n |df          = dmy-all\n}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n{{Wikiquote|Sonny Bill Williams}}\n\n<!-- * [http://www.crfu.co.nz/ Crusaders p